1
00:01:31,892 --> 00:01:35,092
[WIND HOWLING]

2
00:01:42,325 --> 00:01:44,392
[SCAR]
Tell me something, Kimblee...

3
00:01:44,392 --> 00:01:47,125
Do you remember
when we first met?

4
00:01:47,125 --> 00:01:49,392
It seems we've
changed places.

5
00:01:49,392 --> 00:01:51,525
You shouldn't
be so confident.

6
00:01:54,492 --> 00:01:56,625
Kimblee! Damn you!

7
00:01:58,758 --> 00:02:01,525
Tell me why!
Why is Winry here?!

8
00:02:01,525 --> 00:02:03,192
We've finally
got Scar cornered,

9
00:02:03,192 --> 00:02:05,592
and now he's taken her
hostage. Because of you!

10
00:02:05,592 --> 00:02:06,725
Stand aside.

11
00:02:06,725 --> 00:02:08,292
[ED GRUNTS]

12
00:02:10,858 --> 00:02:12,392
What are you doing?!

13
00:02:12,925 --> 00:02:16,525
[ED]
Stop! Stop this now,
Crimson Alchemist!

14
00:02:16,525 --> 00:02:18,425
Can't you see Winry's
up there with him?!

15
00:02:18,425 --> 00:02:20,258
I won't let you attack!

16
00:02:22,692 --> 00:02:25,125
[KIMBLEE]
Why can't you just
stay out of the way?

17
00:02:25,125 --> 00:02:27,158
[SCAR YELLS]

18
00:02:27,525 --> 00:02:28,192
[EXPLOSION]

19
00:02:28,192 --> 00:02:31,458
[SOLDIERS YELLING AND COUGHING]

20
00:02:35,192 --> 00:02:37,125
Not so fast, Ishvalan...

21
00:02:37,125 --> 00:02:38,225
No, wait!

22
00:02:38,225 --> 00:02:40,725
It's much too dangerous
to get close to the building.

23
00:02:42,358 --> 00:02:44,158
[SOLDIER A]
Fall back!

24
00:02:44,158 --> 00:02:45,192
[SOLDIER B]
A snowstorm!

25
00:02:45,192 --> 00:02:46,492
[SOLDIER C]
Hurry!

26
00:02:53,253 --> 00:02:55,309
That was a
convincing performance.

27
00:02:55,309 --> 00:02:57,609
It wasn't a performance.

28
00:02:57,609 --> 00:03:00,276
I'm every bit as angry
as I sounded back there.

29
00:03:00,276 --> 00:03:04,709
I feel so worthless... Having to
put on this stupid charade!

30
00:03:07,209 --> 00:03:11,176
[WINRY]
Why... Why did you kill
my mother and father?

31
00:03:11,176 --> 00:03:15,009
[SCAR]
There's nothing I can say that
won't sound like an excuse...

32
00:03:15,009 --> 00:03:16,709
And nothing can
change the fact

33
00:03:16,709 --> 00:03:20,076
that I am responsible
for their deaths.

34
00:03:20,076 --> 00:03:21,609
I killed them.

35
00:03:28,442 --> 00:03:33,109
Young girl, you have every
right to pass judgment on me.

36
00:03:44,476 --> 00:03:47,676
Your arm... You'll die
if we don't bandage it.

37
00:03:47,676 --> 00:03:48,676
Winry?!

38
00:03:48,676 --> 00:03:51,409
Quiet, Ed.
I think...

39
00:03:51,409 --> 00:03:54,442
I think this is what
my parents would have wanted.

40
00:03:54,442 --> 00:03:56,176
[SCAR SHUDDERS]

41
00:03:57,276 --> 00:04:00,542
Mom and Dad saved
his life before, after all...

42
00:04:00,542 --> 00:04:03,542
There has to be
a reason for that.

43
00:04:03,542 --> 00:04:06,076
Does that...
mean you're forgiving me?

44
00:04:06,076 --> 00:04:07,542
Oh, don't get me wrong!

45
00:04:07,542 --> 00:04:10,142
I don't forgive
your wanton murdering.

46
00:04:10,142 --> 00:04:12,576
[SCAR GRUNTS]

47
00:04:17,442 --> 00:04:19,709
[CLOTH TIGHTENING]

48
00:04:21,709 --> 00:04:23,576
Winry...

49
00:04:23,576 --> 00:04:26,609
It's all right.
I won't cry.

50
00:04:28,142 --> 00:04:30,476
Didn't I promise that
next time I cried...

51
00:04:30,476 --> 00:04:32,576
they would be
tears of joy?

52
00:04:38,309 --> 00:04:39,709
[WINRY LAUGHS LIGHTLY]

53
00:04:42,042 --> 00:04:46,442
[ED]
Listen, Scar!
No matter what Winry says...

54
00:04:46,442 --> 00:04:49,542
I still want to beat you
bloody... and drag you down

55
00:04:49,542 --> 00:04:53,442
to the Rockbell family
grave to pay your respects.

56
00:04:57,409 --> 00:04:59,309
Should we contact
headquarters, sir?

57
00:04:59,309 --> 00:05:00,476
Yes.

58
00:05:00,476 --> 00:05:05,776
[SCAR]
Major Miles, wasn't it?
Can I ask something?

59
00:05:05,776 --> 00:05:07,142
[MILES]
What?

60
00:05:07,742 --> 00:05:10,776
Earlier you said
I was one of your people.

61
00:05:10,776 --> 00:05:11,776
That's right...

62
00:05:11,776 --> 00:05:15,509
I'm part Ishvalan, on
my grandfather's side.

63
00:05:16,576 --> 00:05:19,242
I wish we didn't
have to meet like this...

64
00:05:19,242 --> 00:05:21,476
red-eyed brother of mine...

65
00:05:22,476 --> 00:05:26,042
How can you bring yourself to be
part of the Amestrian military?

66
00:05:26,042 --> 00:05:27,176
[LIAM STAMMERS]

67
00:05:28,742 --> 00:05:31,676
My objective is to work
from the inside to change how

68
00:05:31,676 --> 00:05:34,509
the people of this country
view the people of Ishval.

69
00:05:34,509 --> 00:05:36,042
[SCAR STAMMERS]

70
00:05:38,042 --> 00:05:42,409
I don't think that great a task
will be easy to accomplish.

71
00:05:42,409 --> 00:05:45,676
[MILES]
Who knows how
long it will take.

72
00:05:45,676 --> 00:05:46,742
But still...

73
00:05:46,742 --> 00:05:49,742
my mixed blood gives me
a slight advantage at least.

74
00:05:49,742 --> 00:05:52,509
I'm an Ishvalan pebble
tossed into the ocean

75
00:05:52,509 --> 00:05:55,009
of the Amestrian military...

76
00:05:55,009 --> 00:05:56,209
Maybe in time,

77
00:05:56,209 --> 00:06:00,242
the ripples I create
will become great waves.

78
00:06:01,676 --> 00:06:05,376
And do you want to know what the
most ironic part about it is?

79
00:06:05,376 --> 00:06:09,442
It was an Amestrian who set me
on this path in the first place.

80
00:06:12,809 --> 00:06:14,042
Look at me...

81
00:06:14,042 --> 00:06:18,509
I am a festering wound of hatred
born of the great Ishvalan War.

82
00:06:19,776 --> 00:06:23,509
I'm thankful that there's
someone like you out there.

83
00:06:25,342 --> 00:06:27,076
[LIAM]
Major...

84
00:06:29,176 --> 00:06:31,742
Copy...? Major Miles here...

85
00:06:31,742 --> 00:06:35,442
We captured Scar.
We're holding him in area D.

86
00:06:35,442 --> 00:06:37,476
Inform Kimblee.

87
00:06:40,242 --> 00:06:42,642
[MILES]
Whatever the circumstances
may be between us,

88
00:06:42,642 --> 00:06:44,642
I cannot let you go.

89
00:06:44,642 --> 00:06:47,576
You must accept judgment.

90
00:06:47,576 --> 00:06:49,209
[MARCOH]
Hold on!

91
00:06:49,209 --> 00:06:50,409
Who's there?

92
00:06:51,242 --> 00:06:53,076
[AL]
May!

93
00:06:53,076 --> 00:06:54,642
[ED]
Dr. Marcoh!

94
00:06:54,642 --> 00:06:58,076
Please don't take Scar as
your prisoner. We need him!

95
00:07:01,709 --> 00:07:04,309
This doesn't look good.
The weather's changing.

96
00:07:04,309 --> 00:07:05,676
[KIMBLEE GRUNTS]

97
00:07:05,676 --> 00:07:08,709
[SOLDIER B]
The clouds are moving fast.
A storm's on it's way.

98
00:07:11,376 --> 00:07:13,109
Hurry then.

99
00:07:14,042 --> 00:07:15,776
[MILES]
Deciphering notes, huh?

100
00:07:15,776 --> 00:07:19,276
[MAY]
Yes! It's ground-breaking
research that tries to fuse

101
00:07:19,276 --> 00:07:22,242
Amestrian alchemy
and Xingense alkahestry.

102
00:07:22,242 --> 00:07:24,409
But all of the important
parts are unreadable,

103
00:07:24,409 --> 00:07:26,642
written in
ancient Ishvalan...

104
00:07:26,642 --> 00:07:29,442
Scar's the only one who
can make sense of it...

105
00:07:29,442 --> 00:07:31,142
Don't you see?

106
00:07:31,142 --> 00:07:32,442
Hmm...

107
00:07:33,776 --> 00:07:36,509
So you're the
alkahestry girl, huh?

108
00:07:36,509 --> 00:07:39,209
I have orders to bring
you back to the fort.

109
00:07:39,209 --> 00:07:41,676
Me? But what do
they want with me?!

110
00:07:41,676 --> 00:07:45,309
Don't worry,...You'll receive
a warm welcome, I'm sure...

111
00:07:45,309 --> 00:07:48,676
Well, let me think here.
Scar needs to be kept free...

112
00:07:48,676 --> 00:07:51,742
and it would be just as bad if
they found out that Dr. Marcoh

113
00:07:51,742 --> 00:07:52,976
was here as well.

114
00:07:52,976 --> 00:07:56,209
All right... I think it might
be best if we took you back

115
00:07:56,209 --> 00:07:59,476
to Ft. Briggs to hide you
from senior military staff.

116
00:07:59,476 --> 00:08:02,142
[ED]
Hold on...
What are you saying?!

117
00:08:02,142 --> 00:08:04,709
You mean we're bringing
that monster with us?!

118
00:08:04,709 --> 00:08:08,142
We need to decipher
those notes, right, Elric?

119
00:08:08,142 --> 00:08:11,142
There's not a damn thing
I want that guy's help with.

120
00:08:11,142 --> 00:08:12,409
Just hand him
over to Kimblee!

121
00:08:12,409 --> 00:08:14,276
The transmutation circle.

122
00:08:14,276 --> 00:08:15,142
[ED GRUNTS]

123
00:08:15,142 --> 00:08:17,776
The one this country
was formed to make.

124
00:08:17,776 --> 00:08:18,809
[MILES SIGHS]

125
00:08:18,809 --> 00:08:20,642
I heard all about it from
General Armstrong...

126
00:08:20,642 --> 00:08:22,276
We know something's
about to happen

127
00:08:22,276 --> 00:08:25,509
that will affect all of
Amestris and its people...

128
00:08:25,509 --> 00:08:28,342
We need to know
what the notes say.

129
00:08:28,342 --> 00:08:31,076
[MILES]
That's more important
than anything else.

130
00:08:31,076 --> 00:08:32,309
[ED EXHALES FRUSTRATEDLY]

131
00:08:32,309 --> 00:08:34,376
I heard they're using
the Rockbell girl

132
00:08:34,376 --> 00:08:36,309
as a hostage
against you...

133
00:08:36,309 --> 00:08:38,276
If we act now,
we can disgrace Kimblee

134
00:08:38,276 --> 00:08:41,409
and find some place to hide
her where they can't touch her.

135
00:08:41,409 --> 00:08:44,242
[ED SCOFFS]

136
00:08:46,242 --> 00:08:47,309
[GUN COCKS]

137
00:08:47,309 --> 00:08:48,609
Listen up, Scar...

138
00:08:48,609 --> 00:08:50,276
If you're willing
to work with us,

139
00:08:50,276 --> 00:08:53,142
I'll postpone
your judgment day.

140
00:08:53,142 --> 00:08:54,676
Well?

141
00:08:54,676 --> 00:08:55,542
It doesn't look like

142
00:08:55,542 --> 00:08:58,276
you're going to give
me any other choice.

143
00:08:58,276 --> 00:09:01,442
Yes, I'll help you
decode the notes.

144
00:09:01,442 --> 00:09:03,609
I have your word on that?

145
00:09:03,609 --> 00:09:06,409
You do. I swear on
my Ishvalan blood...

146
00:09:06,409 --> 00:09:09,176
You can trust me,
my red-eyed brother.

147
00:09:09,676 --> 00:09:13,209
We have a deal then...
My apologies, Miss Rockbell...

148
00:09:13,209 --> 00:09:15,309
You'll have to wait
awhile before we can punish

149
00:09:15,309 --> 00:09:17,076
your parents' killer.

150
00:09:17,076 --> 00:09:18,076
Fine.

151
00:09:18,076 --> 00:09:19,776
[GERSO AND ZAMPANO GRUNTING]

152
00:09:19,776 --> 00:09:23,042
Right, I almost forgot about
these two freaks of nature...

153
00:09:23,042 --> 00:09:24,142
Dispose of them.

154
00:09:24,142 --> 00:09:24,676
[MICK]
Yes sir.

155
00:09:24,676 --> 00:09:26,242
Hold on a second!

156
00:09:26,242 --> 00:09:28,676
[AL]
Wait! You don't
have to kill them!

157
00:09:28,676 --> 00:09:32,009
I see no reason to
let them live. Kill them.

158
00:09:32,009 --> 00:09:34,109
No! A life is a life!

159
00:09:34,109 --> 00:09:36,476
What better reason do
you need than that?!

160
00:09:36,476 --> 00:09:37,276
[GERSO SCOFFS]

161
00:09:37,276 --> 00:09:39,709
Showing us mercy.
How adorable.

162
00:09:39,709 --> 00:09:41,376
You're just
a sentimental fool...

163
00:09:41,376 --> 00:09:43,309
We didn't ask for
your help, did we?

164
00:09:43,309 --> 00:09:44,476
[AL STAMMERS]

165
00:09:44,476 --> 00:09:47,009
Look at these bodies. What
kind of future can we have?

166
00:09:47,009 --> 00:09:49,309
If you're going
to kill us, do it!

167
00:09:50,576 --> 00:09:52,142
I don't understand...

168
00:09:52,142 --> 00:09:54,442
Don't you have
families... loved ones?

169
00:09:54,442 --> 00:09:56,009
Sure we do.

170
00:09:56,009 --> 00:09:58,609
But as soon as we got these
bodies, they were all told

171
00:09:58,609 --> 00:10:02,042
that we were dead...
and to them, we are.

172
00:10:02,042 --> 00:10:03,776
[AL]
Don't you want
to see them again?

173
00:10:03,776 --> 00:10:07,542
[ZAMPANO]
Even if we did, how could we
go back to them like this?

174
00:10:07,542 --> 00:10:08,742
[AL EXHALES FRUSTRATEDLY]

175
00:10:08,742 --> 00:10:12,309
So, you don't want to get your
original bodies back then?

176
00:10:12,309 --> 00:10:15,276
You're content the way
you are now? Is that it?!

177
00:10:15,276 --> 00:10:16,576
No, how could we be?!

178
00:10:16,576 --> 00:10:20,142
Of course we want
our true bodies back! Argh!

179
00:10:20,142 --> 00:10:22,242
There's your answer!

180
00:10:22,242 --> 00:10:25,442
I don't want to hear a bunch
of fatalistic nonsense!

181
00:10:25,442 --> 00:10:27,776
Why not live,
and learn whether

182
00:10:27,776 --> 00:10:31,042
there's a chance of
getting your bodies back?

183
00:10:31,042 --> 00:10:34,276
Hmph, how could you possibly
know what we're going through?

184
00:10:34,276 --> 00:10:37,009
And what chance do
we have of going back?

185
00:10:37,009 --> 00:10:38,142
[ZAMPANO GASPS]

186
00:10:39,576 --> 00:10:41,176
[ZAMPANO AND GERSO GASP]

187
00:10:42,276 --> 00:10:46,342
Well, I'm going back...
no matter how long it takes.

188
00:10:46,342 --> 00:10:48,509
I'm not giving up!

189
00:10:49,542 --> 00:10:50,709
[LIAM]
Major!

190
00:10:52,109 --> 00:10:52,776
What is it?

191
00:10:52,776 --> 00:10:55,742
It's not good.
A snowstorm.

192
00:10:55,742 --> 00:10:59,542
We can't complete a snowbound
march with this equipment.

193
00:10:59,542 --> 00:11:02,242
We have no chance
of reaching the fort.

194
00:11:02,809 --> 00:11:04,676
What do we do now?

195
00:11:04,676 --> 00:11:07,009
This is a mining
town, isn't it?

196
00:11:07,009 --> 00:11:09,609
Why don't we just go
into the underground tunnels.

197
00:11:09,609 --> 00:11:10,776
[YOKI WINRY AND MAY]
Huh?!

198
00:11:10,776 --> 00:11:13,076
Wha... what's wrong?

199
00:11:13,076 --> 00:11:15,609
I mean, this is
a pretty large mine, right?

200
00:11:15,609 --> 00:11:17,242
So surely there's
a tunnel that can

201
00:11:17,242 --> 00:11:21,309
take us beyond the
mountains. Uh... I think.

202
00:11:21,309 --> 00:11:22,176
[ED AND AL]
That's it!

203
00:11:22,176 --> 00:11:23,376
[MAY]
Mr. Yoki!

204
00:11:23,376 --> 00:11:26,342
Hey, give me some credit.
This is what I did for a living.

205
00:11:27,042 --> 00:11:30,076
[MICK]
He's right... The tunnels
come out past the mountains.

206
00:11:30,076 --> 00:11:31,576
Right...

207
00:11:31,576 --> 00:11:35,042
Once you run into Briggs
soldiers, just hand them this...

208
00:11:35,809 --> 00:11:37,509
I've explained
our arrangement,

209
00:11:37,509 --> 00:11:39,742
so you shouldn't
have trouble with them.

210
00:11:39,742 --> 00:11:40,909
[MARCOH]
Thank you.

211
00:11:42,176 --> 00:11:45,609
But there's still the matter
of the young Miss Rockbell.

212
00:11:45,609 --> 00:11:48,576
She can accompany us
to the fort, of course...

213
00:11:48,576 --> 00:11:51,109
but when word gets
out that she's missing...

214
00:11:51,109 --> 00:11:55,309
won't the Elric brothers be
the first people they suspect?

215
00:11:55,309 --> 00:11:57,042
We can handle ourselves.

216
00:11:57,042 --> 00:11:58,276
Yeah, I hate to brag...

217
00:11:58,276 --> 00:12:00,409
but I've got a pretty
smooth tongue, you know.

218
00:12:00,409 --> 00:12:02,676
[MILES]
No, this is Kimblee
we're dealing with.

219
00:12:02,676 --> 00:12:04,276
He's very skeptical...

220
00:12:04,276 --> 00:12:06,276
He's automatically
going to be suspicious

221
00:12:06,276 --> 00:12:07,409
of whatever
you tell him.

222
00:12:07,409 --> 00:12:09,509
[ED STAMMERS]

223
00:12:14,709 --> 00:12:21,109
[WINRY]
Um... I hate to be the one to
suggest this... but... uh...

224
00:12:21,109 --> 00:12:22,409
What do you think
Kimblee would do

225
00:12:22,409 --> 00:12:25,509
if I was suddenly
taken hostage by Scar?

226
00:12:25,509 --> 00:12:27,576
[NARRATOR]
Fullmetal Alchemist.

227
00:12:31,974 --> 00:12:33,974
[NARRATOR]
Fullmetal Alchemist.

228
00:12:35,140 --> 00:12:37,107
You want him
to kidnap you?

229
00:12:37,107 --> 00:12:39,274
Hold on, Winry...

230
00:12:39,274 --> 00:12:42,340
you're saying...
You want us to let him go?

231
00:12:42,340 --> 00:12:45,540
[WINRY]
Right... Scar runs
away, carrying me.

232
00:12:45,540 --> 00:12:48,174
Then Ed, you and the others
try desperately to stop him.

233
00:12:48,174 --> 00:12:51,874
Or at least, that's what you
pretend to do... You understand?

234
00:12:51,874 --> 00:12:53,840
You can't do that!
You're crazy!

235
00:12:53,840 --> 00:12:55,574
Well, I don't have
a choice, do I?!

236
00:12:55,574 --> 00:12:57,174
I'm a hostage either way,

237
00:12:57,174 --> 00:12:59,407
so I might as well
get to choose my captor!

238
00:12:59,407 --> 00:13:01,374
[AL]
But he's a mass murderer!

239
00:13:01,374 --> 00:13:02,474
Al's right!

240
00:13:02,474 --> 00:13:05,207
There's no reason for you
to be risking your life!

241
00:13:05,207 --> 00:13:05,940
Don't you get it?!

242
00:13:05,940 --> 00:13:07,440
It's time for
you two to learn

243
00:13:07,440 --> 00:13:09,840
you don't have to
do everything alone!

244
00:13:09,840 --> 00:13:12,807
[ED AND AL GASP]

245
00:13:12,807 --> 00:13:16,807
Make up your minds...
The storm is coming in...

246
00:13:16,807 --> 00:13:19,274
If we don't hurry we won't
be able to get out of here.

247
00:13:19,274 --> 00:13:21,440
[ED BREATHES HEAVILY]

248
00:13:24,274 --> 00:13:26,174
I can see
Kimblee's forces now!

249
00:13:26,174 --> 00:13:27,874
[ED AND WINRY GASP]

250
00:13:27,874 --> 00:13:29,340
[ED GRUNTS ANGRILY]

251
00:13:29,340 --> 00:13:31,440
Damn it!

252
00:13:31,440 --> 00:13:34,507
Scar! If you do
anything to hurt her I'll--

253
00:13:34,507 --> 00:13:37,540
I won't harm the girl...
I keep my promises.

254
00:13:38,874 --> 00:13:40,240
[SMALL EXPLOSION]

255
00:13:42,540 --> 00:13:47,207
[GERSO]
Us, too... Please, you have
to take us with you, too.

256
00:13:48,307 --> 00:13:50,507
I know you
don't trust us...

257
00:13:50,507 --> 00:13:53,840
So I understand if you
want to keep us tied up.

258
00:13:53,840 --> 00:13:55,474
Kimblee shows
no mercy to troops

259
00:13:55,474 --> 00:13:57,374
who fail to
accomplish their missions...

260
00:13:57,374 --> 00:13:59,374
One way or
the other, we're dead...

261
00:13:59,374 --> 00:14:03,140
besides... We don't
want to give up, either.

262
00:14:03,140 --> 00:14:04,440
[AL HEAVILY EXHALES]

263
00:14:06,007 --> 00:14:08,507
How do we know
you mean that?

264
00:14:08,507 --> 00:14:11,974
You realize, if you do
anything to obstruct us...

265
00:14:11,974 --> 00:14:14,507
the whole country
could be destroyed...

266
00:14:14,507 --> 00:14:17,874
Including your families
and everyone you care about.

267
00:14:17,874 --> 00:14:18,807
[ZAMPANO STAMMERS]

268
00:14:18,807 --> 00:14:20,840
Wait, hold on!
Just what are you saying?!

269
00:14:20,840 --> 00:14:21,907
I don't understand.

270
00:14:21,907 --> 00:14:24,107
The Central forces weren't
told about any of this!

271
00:14:24,107 --> 00:14:26,174
Please, we need
to know more!

272
00:14:26,174 --> 00:14:27,940
What's going on?

273
00:14:29,007 --> 00:14:31,807
[PAPERS RUSTLING]

274
00:14:35,407 --> 00:14:37,040
[MILES]
You're sure about this?

275
00:14:37,040 --> 00:14:38,007
Yeah...

276
00:14:38,007 --> 00:14:39,507
I'm sure everyone will
feel a whole lot better

277
00:14:39,507 --> 00:14:41,440
if we're tied up.

278
00:14:41,440 --> 00:14:44,874
All right, Scar...
Give us a good performance.

279
00:14:44,874 --> 00:14:46,407
I know what I'm doing.

280
00:14:46,407 --> 00:14:48,174
And you will
keep your oath...

281
00:14:48,174 --> 00:14:51,307
Your solemn word
as a true Ishvalan.

282
00:14:51,307 --> 00:14:52,907
[SCAR GRUNTS IN AGREEMENT]

283
00:14:56,607 --> 00:15:00,107
Excuse me,
Miss... Your ears!

284
00:15:00,107 --> 00:15:02,240
Your earrings are
made out of metal...

285
00:15:02,240 --> 00:15:04,374
If you don't take them out,
you'll get frostbite.

286
00:15:04,374 --> 00:15:05,540
Oh...

287
00:15:13,374 --> 00:15:14,407
[WINRY]
Ed...

288
00:15:16,240 --> 00:15:18,240
You hang onto these for me.

289
00:15:20,074 --> 00:15:22,407
I'll see you
back at the fort!

290
00:15:29,140 --> 00:15:31,140
[LARGE EXPLOSION]

291
00:15:31,140 --> 00:15:33,274
[ED COUGHING]

292
00:15:33,274 --> 00:15:34,940
We've finally
got Scar cornered,

293
00:15:34,940 --> 00:15:37,774
and now he's taken
her hostage. Because of you!

294
00:15:41,225 --> 00:15:45,392
[WIND HOWLING]

295
00:15:49,258 --> 00:15:50,992
[ED GRUNTS]

296
00:15:52,793 --> 00:15:55,345
I'm worried about what's
happened to Zampano and Gerso.

297
00:15:55,345 --> 00:15:56,811
There are
two possibilities...

298
00:15:56,811 --> 00:15:59,611
Either Scar did them in, or
they're out there in the snow.

299
00:15:59,611 --> 00:16:01,578
[SOLDIER B]
The storm will have
Scar trapped, too.

300
00:16:01,578 --> 00:16:04,411
We know he has to be
somewhere in this town, sir...

301
00:16:04,411 --> 00:16:05,478
Since we're stuck here,

302
00:16:05,478 --> 00:16:07,845
we might as well start
planning our next search.

303
00:16:08,845 --> 00:16:12,678
[MILES THINKING]
We got lucky... This storm
really saved our hides...

304
00:16:12,678 --> 00:16:15,011
Please let them
reach the fort safely.

305
00:16:16,445 --> 00:16:17,878
Excuse me, Major...

306
00:16:17,878 --> 00:16:20,245
Briggs is on
the line for you.

307
00:16:23,011 --> 00:16:24,678
Yes, Miles here.

308
00:16:26,611 --> 00:16:28,278
Eh, What'd you say?!

309
00:16:32,978 --> 00:16:34,045
So it's true, then?

310
00:16:34,045 --> 00:16:36,978
You're actually the daughter
of the Doctors Rockbell?

311
00:16:36,978 --> 00:16:39,745
Yes. Did you know
my parents, Dr. Marcoh?

312
00:16:39,745 --> 00:16:41,978
Of course I did.
There isn't a single doctor

313
00:16:41,978 --> 00:16:45,345
who worked in Ishval that
didn't know your parents' names.

314
00:16:45,345 --> 00:16:49,345
They did their duty, without
any regard to themselves.

315
00:16:51,711 --> 00:16:54,311
I don't forgive
your wanton murdering.

316
00:16:55,811 --> 00:16:58,011
[MASTER]
This is something
you must abide.

317
00:16:58,011 --> 00:17:01,611
How can I forgive the military
for all that they've done?

318
00:17:01,611 --> 00:17:03,911
I said nothing
about forgiveness...

319
00:17:03,911 --> 00:17:06,545
There is no forgiveness
for wanton murder.

320
00:17:06,545 --> 00:17:10,311
Any good man must always
condemn it... but still...

321
00:17:10,311 --> 00:17:12,011
you must abide it...

322
00:17:12,011 --> 00:17:15,711
You must sever the chain of
hatred once and for all.

323
00:17:15,711 --> 00:17:17,978
If hatred and fear
are allowed to prevail,

324
00:17:17,978 --> 00:17:20,445
the world will be
swallowed by them.

325
00:17:20,445 --> 00:17:22,978
But if ultimate
understanding can be reached,

326
00:17:22,978 --> 00:17:26,878
we may still have a chance
to be saved from ourselves.

327
00:17:26,878 --> 00:17:31,478
That is my motivation...
that's why I study alchemy.

328
00:17:34,678 --> 00:17:36,811
[YOKI]
Yep...
this is it, all right.

329
00:17:39,932 --> 00:17:41,459
Okay. What is
this place?

330
00:17:41,459 --> 00:17:44,392
The mine's staff room.
We need something from here...

331
00:17:44,392 --> 00:17:47,559
Now let's see...
Ah...! Here it is.

332
00:17:47,559 --> 00:17:50,559
[YOKI]
See...? A detailed
map of the tunnels.

333
00:17:50,559 --> 00:17:54,159
[GERSO]
Looks complicated.
I can't tell what's what.

334
00:17:54,159 --> 00:17:57,326
We go through here, here,
and here... and we're out!

335
00:17:57,326 --> 00:17:59,426
Impressive. You sure
know how to read a map!

336
00:17:59,426 --> 00:18:00,326
[YOKI LAUGHING]

337
00:18:00,326 --> 00:18:02,159
Oh, it's nothing.

338
00:18:02,159 --> 00:18:03,892
[GERSO]
At this rate, we
should make it over to

339
00:18:03,892 --> 00:18:04,826
the other side
of the mountain

340
00:18:04,826 --> 00:18:07,226
a lot quicker than
we had first thought.

341
00:18:07,926 --> 00:18:09,892
Uh, excuse me,
Dr. Marcoh...?

342
00:18:09,892 --> 00:18:11,992
Are there any hints in
those research notes you have

343
00:18:11,992 --> 00:18:14,426
about how we might try
getting out original forms back?

344
00:18:14,426 --> 00:18:16,292
At the moment,
I can't say...

345
00:18:16,292 --> 00:18:17,359
It's a possibility,

346
00:18:17,359 --> 00:18:20,359
but this is a form of
alchemy I know nothing about.

347
00:18:20,359 --> 00:18:22,092
I'm sure you'll
find a way, Doc!

348
00:18:22,092 --> 00:18:24,992
Ah! I can't wait to
see my family again!

349
00:18:24,992 --> 00:18:25,926
[ZAMPANO LAUGHS]

350
00:18:25,926 --> 00:18:26,826
Are you really that eager

351
00:18:26,826 --> 00:18:29,059
to get back to
the old ball and chain?

352
00:18:29,059 --> 00:18:31,926
I'm sure you miss your daughter,
but I doubt you miss your wife.

353
00:18:31,926 --> 00:18:34,026
What about you?
You were such a lousy drunk

354
00:18:34,026 --> 00:18:35,926
your own son couldn't
stand to be around you

355
00:18:35,926 --> 00:18:37,026
for more than five minutes...

356
00:18:37,026 --> 00:18:40,159
and you really think
you'll be able to face him now?

357
00:18:40,159 --> 00:18:42,126
[ZAMPANO]
You have to bring that up?

358
00:18:42,126 --> 00:18:44,159
[ZAMPANO AND GERSO LAUGHING]

359
00:18:44,159 --> 00:18:46,292
Are you all right,
May? What's wrong?

360
00:18:46,292 --> 00:18:48,459
It's just...

361
00:18:48,459 --> 00:18:51,626
My entire clan is waiting
for me back in my country,

362
00:18:51,626 --> 00:18:54,292
but I don't think
I can return to them.

363
00:18:57,126 --> 00:19:00,926
The Philosopher's Stone is made
from sacrificing people's lives.

364
00:19:00,926 --> 00:19:04,326
No one should be allowed to
create something so awful.

365
00:19:04,326 --> 00:19:07,459
If His Imperial Highness
found out how to make one...

366
00:19:07,459 --> 00:19:11,426
He wouldn't hesitate
a moment to do it.

367
00:19:11,426 --> 00:19:16,059
He'd be willing to sacrifice
any number of our people.

368
00:19:16,059 --> 00:19:19,592
But we need it...
What am I supposed to do now?

369
00:19:19,592 --> 00:19:21,392
It's possible
these notes contain

370
00:19:21,392 --> 00:19:25,426
what you're looking for:
a humane secret to immortality.

371
00:19:25,426 --> 00:19:29,259
Let's hurry to the fort and
figure out what they say.

372
00:19:29,259 --> 00:19:30,392
Right.

373
00:19:30,392 --> 00:19:33,026
[ED]
What do you mean
"the fort is no longer safe"?!

374
00:19:33,026 --> 00:19:34,926
I mean that
General Armstrong's been

375
00:19:34,926 --> 00:19:37,059
summoned back to the
Central Command Center.

376
00:19:37,059 --> 00:19:38,192
Troops sent from Central

377
00:19:38,192 --> 00:19:40,426
have begun
invading Briggs in force...

378
00:19:40,426 --> 00:19:41,626
There's no doubt
they're acting

379
00:19:41,626 --> 00:19:43,626
on the Crimson
Alchemist's orders...

380
00:19:43,626 --> 00:19:44,726
When we were
back at the fort,

381
00:19:44,726 --> 00:19:48,426
I noticed him making
rather frequent phone calls.

382
00:19:48,426 --> 00:19:52,026
This is bad. Without
General Armstrong there...

383
00:19:52,026 --> 00:19:54,092
[MILES]
A commander
hand-picked by Bradley

384
00:19:54,092 --> 00:19:55,892
will be posted in her place.

385
00:19:55,892 --> 00:19:57,592
What do we do
about Winry?!

386
00:19:57,592 --> 00:20:00,259
Hiding her and
the others will be difficult...

387
00:20:00,259 --> 00:20:01,326
If they're not careful,

388
00:20:01,326 --> 00:20:04,259
they're bound to fall
into the enemy's clutches.

389
00:20:06,159 --> 00:20:07,126
[ED EXHALES FRUSTRATEDLY]

390
00:20:07,126 --> 00:20:10,359
[ED]
We have to find
some way to warn them!

391
00:20:10,359 --> 00:20:13,992
There's no way we can catch up
to them in a storm this bad.

392
00:20:13,992 --> 00:20:15,626
So we sit here
and do nothing?!

393
00:20:15,626 --> 00:20:16,726
I'll go tell them!

394
00:20:16,726 --> 00:20:19,559
Don't go underestimating
the storm out there, kid...

395
00:20:19,559 --> 00:20:22,192
You'll freeze to death
before you come anywhere close

396
00:20:22,192 --> 00:20:24,392
to reaching them.

397
00:20:24,392 --> 00:20:27,226
[AL]
There is a way... Listen.

398
00:20:27,226 --> 00:20:29,859
Send someone who
doesn't have a body...

399
00:20:29,859 --> 00:20:32,426
That storm won't
freeze me to death.

400
00:20:33,892 --> 00:20:36,126
[STRONG WIND BLOWING]

401
00:20:36,126 --> 00:20:41,226
[AL BREATHING HEAVILY]

402
00:20:41,226 --> 00:20:43,626
This is worse than I thought.

403
00:20:43,626 --> 00:20:46,859
Let's see...
the marker, the marker...

404
00:20:47,659 --> 00:20:49,192
There!

405
00:20:49,192 --> 00:20:55,159
[AL PAINFULLY GRUNTS]

406
00:20:55,159 --> 00:20:57,992
I can't see anything at all!

407
00:20:59,926 --> 00:21:01,026
[AL SHUDDERS]

408
00:21:03,592 --> 00:21:04,592
[AL GASPS]

409
00:21:15,059 --> 00:21:18,459
[AL STAMMERS]

410
00:21:22,259 --> 00:21:24,892
[STRONG WIND BLOWING]

411
00:21:24,892 --> 00:21:31,025
What was that?!
Was it my body?! But how...?

412
00:21:32,026 --> 00:21:33,626
[66]
I guess a body
just can't hold up

413
00:21:33,626 --> 00:21:36,959
with someone else's soul
being shoved inside of it.

414
00:21:37,592 --> 00:21:41,426
[AL]
A body... a body that
shouldn't have a soul in it...

415
00:21:41,426 --> 00:21:43,559
It's being rejected?

416
00:21:44,659 --> 00:21:48,092
Does this mean my body
is pulling on my soul?

417
00:21:48,092 --> 00:21:52,492
[AL BREATHES HEAVILY]

418
00:21:52,492 --> 00:21:55,059
Stop it...! Snap out of it!

419
00:21:58,426 --> 00:22:00,426
I have to hurry!

420
00:22:04,326 --> 00:22:06,592
[FATHER]
Alphonse Elric...

421
00:22:09,426 --> 00:22:12,026
Edward Elric...

422
00:22:14,026 --> 00:22:16,426
And also...

423
00:22:16,426 --> 00:22:20,592
There's...
Van Hohenheim...

424
00:22:20,592 --> 00:22:24,959
Izumi Curtis...
She's a possibility.

425
00:22:29,559 --> 00:22:32,492
That leaves one more.

426
00:24:04,026 --> 00:24:06,592
[NARRATOR]
"A journey into
an unknown world."

427
00:24:06,592 --> 00:24:09,959
The spirit desperately
searching for something new.

428
00:24:10,992 --> 00:24:13,459
Nobody can stop
the spirit's quest...

429
00:24:13,459 --> 00:24:18,859
but that journey... is not
without consequences of its own.

430
00:24:18,859 --> 00:24:22,092
Next time, on Fullmetal
Alchemist: Brotherhood...

431
00:24:22,092 --> 00:24:25,892
Episode 40: "Homunculus."

432
00:24:25,892 --> 00:24:28,626
He who is right
does not always win.

433
00:24:28,626 --> 00:24:32,426
It is he who overcomes all
barriers who will prevail.

